TITLE: Structuring JSON Metadata for Multiple Excel Custom Functions
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet demonstrates the overall structure for defining multiple custom functions within a single metadata file. It includes the `$schema` property pointing to the official Office JS custom functions schema and a `functions` array. Each element in the `functions` array is an object defining the metadata (like `id` and `name`) for a specific custom function, such as "ADD" and "INCREMENT".
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/excel/custom-functions-json.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "$schema": "https://developer.microsoft.com/json-schemas/office-js/custom-functions.schema.json",
  "functions": [
    {
      "id": "ADD",
      "name": "ADD",
      ...
    },
    {
      "id": "INCREMENT",
      "name": "INCREMENT",
      ...
    }
  ]
}
```

