TITLE: Including Office JS Library from CDN in HTML Head
DESCRIPTION: This HTML snippet shows how to reference the core Office JavaScript API library from the Microsoft CDN within the `<head>` section of an add-in's web page. Including this script tag is essential to enable the use of Office JavaScript APIs. The `src` attribute points to the standard production library. For preview APIs, the URL `https://appsforoffice.microsoft.com/lib/beta/hosted/office.js` should be used instead.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/includes/office-js-access-library.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<head>
    ...
    <script src="https://appsforoffice.microsoft.com/lib/1/hosted/office.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
</head>
```

