TITLE: Formatting the Current Item ID for REST APIs in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to retrieve the current Outlook item's ID, ensuring it is properly formatted for the REST API. The function checks the Office.context.mailbox.diagnostics.hostName to determine if conversion is needed; in Outlook on iOS, the itemId is already REST-formatted, while in other clients, Office.context.mailbox.convertToRestId is used along with the required REST API version. Depends on Office.js and the availability of the item context. Returns a string identifier compatible with REST URLs and is required to avoid issues with non-URL safe characters from legacy ID formats.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/outlook/use-rest-api.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function getItemRestId() {\n  if (Office.context.mailbox.diagnostics.hostName === 'OutlookIOS') {\n    // itemId is already REST-formatted.\n    return Office.context.mailbox.item.itemId;\n  } else {\n    // Convert to an item ID for API v2.0.\n    return Office.context.mailbox.convertToRestId(\n      Office.context.mailbox.item.itemId,\n      Office.MailboxEnums.RestVersion.v2_0\n    );\n  }\n}
```

