TITLE: Insert Range and Shift Cells Down in Excel using JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to insert a new range of cells ('B4:E4') into the 'Sample' worksheet using the Excel JavaScript API. It utilizes the `range.insert` method with the `Excel.InsertShiftDirection.down` option, which causes the existing cells below the insertion point to be shifted downwards to accommodate the new, empty range.
