TITLE: Checking Keyboard Shortcut Availability with Office.js - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use Office.actions.areShortcutsInUse to check whether specific keyboard combinations are already in use in an Office Add-in's context. By passing an array of shortcut strings, it asynchronously obtains a report and segregates the available and used shortcuts, using filter on the result. Useful for avoiding conflicts between add-ins or with native Office shortcuts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/design/keyboard-shortcuts.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const shortcuts = ["Ctrl+Shift+1", "Ctrl+Shift+2"];
