TITLE: Retrieving and Setting Data for Addin Field - Office.js - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This sample demonstrates how to retrieve the first Addin field in the active Word document and how to set its data property using Office.js. It filters for Addin types, loads the fields collection, accesses the first item, displays its original data, then sets the data property to a specified value and confirms the change. The pattern uses context.sync for async state management and provides robust handling for cases where no appropriate field exists.
