TITLE: Registering Workbook Activation Event Handler with Excel JavaScript API - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code sample explains how to subscribe to the 'onActivated' event of an Excel workbook and specify a callback for when the workbook is activated. It includes registering the handler and a sample callback function that loads and logs the name of the activated workbook. Dependencies are Office.js and a runtime supporting async/await. Input is the event trigger; output is a console log with the workbook name. Registration and callback must happen within the context of an Excel add-in.
