TITLE: Adding Office JS Binding from Named Item (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This function demonstrates how to create a 'matrix' type binding associated with a pre-existing named item called 'myRange' in the Office document. It uses the `addFromNamedItemAsync` method, assigns the ID 'myMatrix' to the new binding, and logs the result or error message using a helper `write` function. Requires the Office JS API and an existing named item 'myRange'.
