TITLE: Summing Numbers Efficiently in Excel Custom Functions - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a custom function called Add that sums an array of numbers efficiently with minimal nesting. It is attributed with @customfunction for Excel add-in recognition. The function accepts a single parameter args (an array of numbers), loops through the values, and returns their sum. Dependencies include the Office JavaScript API with support for custom functions. Input is an array of numbers; output is their summed value as a number. Best used for bulk addition without excessive nesting.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/excel/custom-functions-get-started.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
/**
* Returns the sum of input numbers.
* @customfunction
*/
function Add(args: number[]): number {
  let total = 0;
  args.forEach(value => {
    total += value;
  });

  return total;
}
```

