TITLE: Handling OBO Flow Errors, Specifically Token Expiration, in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Implements the error handling (`catch` block) for the OBO flow and Graph call. It specifically checks if the error message contains the `AADSTS500133` code, which indicates an expired assertion token during the OBO exchange. If detected, it sends a 401 status (Unauthorized) so the client application can attempt to refresh the SSO token and retry. Other errors result in a generic 403 status (Forbidden) response.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/develop/create-sso-office-add-ins-nodejs.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
} catch (err) {
   // On rare occasions the SSO access token is unexpired when Office validates it,
   // but expires by the time it is used in the OBO flow. Microsoft identity platform will respond
   // with "The provided value for the 'assertion' is not valid. The assertion has expired."
   // Construct an error message to return to the client so it can refresh the SSO token.
   if (err.errorMessage.indexOf('AADSTS500133') !== -1) {
     res.status(401).send({ type: "TokenExpiredError", errorDetails: err });
   } else {
     res.status(403).send({ type: "Unknown", errorDetails: err });
   }
}
```

