TITLE: Implementing Outlook Signature Event Handlers in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines JavaScript event handlers (`onNewMessageComposeHandler`, `onMessageFromChangedHandler`) for an Outlook add-in using the Office JS API. `onNewMessageComposeHandler` conditionally adds a default signature to new messages if no client signature is enabled (platform check included). `onMessageFromChangedHandler` retrieves the selected 'From' account details, creates a signature including an embedded image, and updates the message body when the sender changes. The `setSignature` function is a helper to apply the signature using `setSignatureAsync`. `Office.actions.associate` maps these functions to action IDs defined in the add-in manifest, enabling event-based activation.
