TITLE: Registering Dialog Message Handler with Error Handling Callback (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code provides a more robust way to register the dialog message handler by including a callback function (`onRegisterMessageComplete`) with `addHandlerAsync`. This callback checks the `asyncResult.status` to verify if the handler registration was successful. If registration fails (`asyncResult.status !== Office.AsyncResultStatus.Succeeded`), it calls a `reportError` function (not defined here) to log or display the error details.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/develop/dialog-api-in-office-add-ins.md#_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
Office.onReady(() => {
    Office.context.ui.addHandlerAsync(
        Office.EventType.DialogParentMessageReceived,
        onMessageFromParent,
        onRegisterMessageComplete
    );
});

