TITLE: Toggling Event Firing in Excel JavaScript Runtime
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to enable or disable event firing globally within the Excel add-in runtime. It uses `Excel.run`, loads the current state of `context.runtime.enableEvents`, toggles the boolean value, assigns it back to `context.runtime.enableEvents`, and then synchronizes the context to apply the change. Console messages indicate the resulting state (on or off).
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/excel/excel-add-ins-events.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
await Excel.run(async (context) => {
    context.runtime.load("enableEvents");
    await context.sync();

    let eventBoolean = !context.runtime.enableEvents;
    context.runtime.enableEvents = eventBoolean;
    if (eventBoolean) {
        console.log("Events are currently on.");
    } else {
        console.log("Events are currently off.");
    }

    await context.sync();
});
```

