TITLE: Retrieving a Specific File Slice using getSliceAsync (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Defines the `getSlice` function which retrieves a single slice from the `File` object using `File.getSliceAsync`. It takes the state object (containing the file and current slice counter) as input. On success, it calls `sendSlice` with the retrieved `Slice` object and the state. It handles potential errors by updating the status.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/develop/get-the-whole-document-from-an-add-in-for-powerpoint-or-word.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
// Get a slice from the file and then call sendSlice.
function getSlice(state) {
    state.file.getSliceAsync(state.counter, function (result) {
        if (result.status == Office.AsyncResultStatus.Succeeded) {
            updateStatus("Sending piece " + (state.counter + 1) + " of " + state.sliceCount);
            sendSlice(result.value, state);
        } else {
            updateStatus(result.status);
        }
    });
}
```

