TITLE: Retrieving a Specific File Slice in an Office Add-in (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This function retrieves a specific slice of the document file using the `file.getSliceAsync` method, based on the current counter in the `state` object. On successful retrieval, it updates the status and calls the `sendSlice` function, passing the retrieved slice data and the current state. It requires the `state` object (containing the file object and counter) as input and depends on `updateStatus` and `sendSlice`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/develop/get-the-whole-document-from-an-add-in-for-powerpoint-or-word.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Get a slice from the file and then call sendSlice.
function getSlice(state) {
    state.file.getSliceAsync(state.counter, function (result) {
        if (result.status == Office.AsyncResultStatus.Succeeded) {
            updateStatus("Sending piece " + (state.counter + 1) + " of " + state.sliceCount);
            sendSlice(result.value, state);
        } else {
            updateStatus(result.status);
        }
    });
}
```

