TITLE: Setting Table Cell Alignment with Office.js in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set horizontal and vertical alignment for specific cells in a PowerPoint table using Office.js. It configures a table to display left/top, centered, and right/bottom aligned text using the TableCellProperties and enumerations like ParagraphHorizontalAlignment. Dependencies include the PowerPoint JavaScript API and a helper function insertTableOnCurrentSlide; the table's alignment is set via options.specificCellProperties for targeted customization.
