TITLE: Getting Access Token with SSO/Fallback in getAccessToken using JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet, for the `getAccessToken` function, implements the logic to retrieve an access token. It checks the `authSSO` boolean flag. If true, it attempts to get the token using `Office.auth.getAccessToken` with SSO options, handling errors with the `handleSSOErrors` function. If `authSSO` is false or if SSO fails and `handleSSOErrors` triggers fallback, it calls `getAccessTokenMSAL` to get the token via MSAL. It throws an error if both SSO and MSAL fallback fail.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/develop/create-sso-office-add-ins-nodejs.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
if (authSSO) {
    try {
        // Get the access token from Office host using SSO.
        // Note that Office.auth.getAccessToken modifies the options parameter. Create a copy of the object
        // to avoid modifying the original object.
        const options = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(ssoOptions));
        const token = await Office.auth.getAccessToken(options);
        return token;
    } catch (error) {
        console.log(error.message);
        return handleSSOErrors(error);
    }
} else {
    // Get access token through MSAL fallback.
    try {
        const accessToken = await getAccessTokenMSAL();
        return accessToken;
    } catch (error) {
