TITLE: Populating Word Content Binding Using Office.js in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet shows how to populate a binding in a Word document add-in using Office.js. It loads OOXML content from a given file using a synchronous XMLHttpRequest, then writes the content into a binding identified by ID ('myBinding'), replacing any existing content in that binding. The only dependency is Office.js, and the main parameter is the filename pointing to the OOXML file. Expected input is the filename (string), and the output is the replacement of the binding's content. The code should not be used in environments where synchronous XMLHttpRequest is not supported or discouraged.
