TITLE: Setting Location using location.setAsync in Office JS
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code sets the location of an Outlook appointment in compose mode using `item.location.setAsync`. It sets the location to the string "Conference room A" (up to 255 characters), overwriting any existing location. The example includes passing optional `asyncContext` and using a callback function to handle the operation's success or failure status. Multiple locations can be set using a semi-colon separator. Requires the Office JavaScript API and jQuery.
