TITLE: Defining an Optional Parameter in a JavaScript Custom Function
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code defines an Excel custom function `add` that takes two required numbers and one optional number. If the third parameter `third` is omitted by the user, Excel passes `null`. The function checks for `null` and defaults it to 0 before calculating the sum. The JSDoc comment `@param {number} [third]` marks the parameter as optional.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/excel/custom-functions-parameter-options.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
/**
 * Calculates the sum of the specified numbers
 * @customfunction
 * @param {number} first First number.
 * @param {number} second Second number.
 * @param {number} [third] Third number to add. If omitted, third = 0.
 * @returns {number} The sum of the numbers.
 */
function add(first, second, third) {
  if (third === null) {
    third = 0;
  }
  return first + second + third;
}
```

