TITLE: Creating AnalyzeUnicode REST Endpoint Using Shared Library (ASP.NET Core, C#)
DESCRIPTION: This C# ASP.NET Core controller method exposes a REST endpoint for Unicode analysis. It handles GET requests at /api/analyzeunicode, validates the 'value' query parameter, and calls the shared library's 'GetUnicodeFromText' method. On success, it returns a string with character Unicode codes; on missing input, it returns HTTP 400. Dependencies: ASP.NET Core, CellAnalyzerSharedLibrary reference.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/tutorials/migrate-vsto-to-office-add-in-shared-code-library-tutorial.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
[HttpGet]
public ActionResult<string> AnalyzeUnicode(string value)
{
  if (value == null)
  {
    return BadRequest();
  }
  return CellAnalyzerSharedLibrary.CellOperations.GetUnicodeFromText(value);
}
```

