TITLE: Converting Selected File to Base64 using JavaScript FileReader
DESCRIPTION: This asynchronous JavaScript function `storeFileAsBase64` uses the `FileReader` API to read the content of the file selected via the input element with ID 'file'. It converts the file content into a base64-encoded data URL. The `onload` event handler extracts the pure base64 string (removing the 'data:...' prefix) and stores it in the global variable `chosenFileBase64` for later use.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/powerpoint/insert-slides-into-presentation.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let chosenFileBase64;

async function storeFileAsBase64() {
    const reader = new FileReader();

    reader.onload = async (event) => {
        const startIndex = reader.result.toString().indexOf("base64,");
        const copyBase64 = reader.result.toString().substr(startIndex + 7);

        chosenFileBase64 = copyBase64;
    };

    const myFile = document.getElementById("file") as HTMLInputElement;
    reader.readAsDataURL(myFile.files[0]);
}
```

