TITLE: Defining CopyWebpackPlugin with Conditional Manifest Transformation - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows a detailed CopyWebpackPlugin setup, copying CSS, assets, and manifest files to the build output. The manifest is conditionally transformed based on the build type (development or production), with URLs swapped accordingly. The patterns array ensures all required static resources are present in the output. Inputs are CSS, assets, and manifest JSON/XML files; outputs are the same assets in the output directory. This object should be included in the plugins array of webpack.config.js.
