TITLE: Processing Typed Messages from Dialog and Branching Workflow - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Receives a JSON message from the dialog, inspects the messageType property to distinguish between sign-in success or failure, and accordingly closes the dialog, shows the user name, redirects, or displays an error notification. This pattern enables multiplexing message handling over a single event. Inputs include the event argument; outputs are dialog closure, UI updates, and potential navigation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/develop/dialog-api-in-office-add-ins.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function processMessage(arg) {
    const messageFromDialog = JSON.parse(arg.message);
    if (messageFromDialog.messageType === "signinSuccess") {
        dialog.close();
        showUserName(messageFromDialog.profile.name);
        window.location.replace("/newPage.html");
    } else {
        dialog.close();
        showNotification("Unable to authenticate user: " + messageFromDialog.error);
    }
}
```

