TITLE: Getting the Next Worksheet Relative to Active with Excel JavaScript API
DESCRIPTION: Finds and references the worksheet immediately following the currently active worksheet using the `getNext()` method called on the active worksheet object. It loads the next sheet's 'name' and logs it. This will throw an `ItemNotFound` error if the active worksheet is the last one in the workbook.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/excel/excel-add-ins-worksheets.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
await Excel.run(async (context) => {
    let currentSheet = context.workbook.worksheets.getActiveWorksheet();
    let nextSheet = currentSheet.getNext();
