DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to programmatically enable a specific ribbon button at runtime using JavaScript. It constructs a `RibbonUpdaterData` object specifying the target tab (`OfficeAppTab1`), group (`CustomGroup111`), and control (`MyButton`) along with the desired enabled status (`true`), and then calls `Office.ribbon.requestUpdate()` to apply the change. This requires the add-in to use a shared runtime and RibbonApi 1.1.
