TITLE: Getting Active Project GUID Asynchronously in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines the `getProjectGuid` function which asynchronously retrieves the GUID of the currently active project using `Office.context.document.getProjectFieldAsync` with the `Office.ProjectProjectFields.GUID` field identifier. Upon successful completion, it stores the retrieved GUID in the global `_projectUid` variable. Handles potential errors during the asynchronous call by invoking the `throwError` function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/project/create-a-project-add-in-that-uses-rest-with-an-on-premises-odata-service.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
// Get the GUID of the active project.
function getProjectGuid() {
    Office.context.document.getProjectFieldAsync(
        Office.ProjectProjectFields.GUID,
        function (asyncResult) {
            if (asyncResult.status == Office.AsyncResultStatus.Succeeded) {
                _projectUid = asyncResult.value.fieldValue;
            }
            else {
                throwError(asyncResult.error.name, asyncResult.error.message);
            }
        }
    );
}
```

