TITLE: Removing Inline Unicode Conversion Logic in VSTO Add-in (C#)
DESCRIPTION: This C# code snippet demonstrates how the VSTO Add-in previously converted cell text to a Unicode character listing using a local for-each loop. It depended only on string concatenation and iteration, which has since been centralized in a shared library for maintainability. The logic processes a given 'cellValue', converting each character to its corresponding Unicode code, and appends the results to a 'result' string, outputting a string representation line by line.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-js-docs-pr/blob/main/docs/tutorials/migrate-vsto-to-office-add-in-shared-code-library-tutorial.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
//Convert to Unicode listing
