TITLE: Passing Access Token to Server-Side API with AJAX Call - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to send an obtained access token to a web API by including it in the Authorization header of an AJAX POST request. Dependencies include jQuery for AJAX functionality. It expects a valid accessToken variable to be set, and a target server endpoint. The function allows for custom JSON data payloads and handles standard AJAX success, failure, and cleanup callbacks. Security recommendation: Always send tokens over secure HTTPS endpoints and do not expose tokens to unauthorized clients.
