TITLE: Retrieving an Access Token Using Office.js in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use Office.context.mailbox.getCallbackTokenAsync with the isRest: true option to asynchronously retrieve a REST-compatible access token for Outlook add-ins. No explicit dependencies are required beyond Office.js, but optionally a callback such as getCurrentItem may be needed to process the token. The method takes an options object and a result callback; upon success, the result contains the access token in result.value, which can be used for further REST API calls. This token is generally read-only for the item unless the add-in manifest requests additional mailbox permissions.
